a224e6d15740b9b07c108e089c84520", "rule_source": "Sigma Integrated Rule Set (GitHub)", "rule_title": "Boot Configuration Tampering Via Bcdedit.EXE", "rule_description": "Detects the use of the bcdedit command to tamper with the boot configuration data. This technique is often times used by malware or attackers as a destructive way before launching ransomware.", "rule_author": "E.M. Anhaus (originally from Atomic Blue Detections, Endgame), oscd.community", "match_context": [{"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\bcdedit.exe\" /set {default} bootstatuspolicy ignoreallfailures", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\bcdedit.exe", "EventID": "1"}}, {"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\bcdedit.exe\" /set {default} recoveryenabled no", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\bcdedit.exe", "EventID": "1"}}]}, {"rule_level": "high", "rule_id": "4b8a086b898ff9eb51b0489b98e2619d0c9fe2cd94e29325ec8a4c2250220b8e", "rule_source": "Sigma Integrated Rule Set (GitHub)", "rule_title": "Fsutil Suspicious Invocation", "rule_description": "Detects suspicious parameters of fsutil (deleting USN journal, configuring it with small size, etc).\nMight be used by ransomwares during the attack (seen by NotPetya and others).\n", "rule_author": "Ecco, E.M. Anhaus, oscd.community", "match_context": [{"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\fsutil.exe\" usn deletejournal /D C:", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\fsutil.exe", "EventID": "1"}}]}, {"rule_level": "high", "rule_id": "ad5e4d4b939797a70a9aa742d979a4742c2cfedddd663fb1a43b2795c1e6054b", "rule_source": "Sigma Integrated Rule Set (GitHub)", "rule_title": "Shadow Copies Deletion Using Operating Systems Utilities", "rule_description": "Shadow Copies deletion using operating systems utilities", "rule_author": "Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Michael Haag, Teymur Kheirkhabarov, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, oscd.community, Andreas Hunkeler (@Karneades)", "match_context": [{"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\wbadmin.exe\" delete catalog -quiet", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\wbadmin.exe", "EventID": "1"}}]}, {"rule_level": "high", "rule_id": "b8f19be4c7bf862dce0d4d1f7885f2207ddf93b3a33d8a6e16f3968c4fbb6491", "rule_source": "Sigma Integrated Rule Set (GitHub)", "rule_title": "Suspicious Eventlog Clear or Configuration Change", "rule_description": "Detects clearing or configuration of eventlogs using wevtutil, powershell and wmic. Might be used by ransomwares during the attack (seen by NotPetya and others).", "rule_author": "Ecco, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, oscd.community, D3F7A5105", "match_context": [{"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe\" cl Application", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe", "EventID": "1"}}, {"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe\" cl System", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe", "EventID": "1"}}, {"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe\" cl Setup", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe", "EventID": "1"}}, {"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe\" cl Security", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe", "EventID": "1"}}, {"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe\" sl Security /e:false", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe", "EventID": "1"}}]}, {"rule_level": "high", "rule_id": "d85308a28516fa075ee74a4ffd11aea2be1f15add944422ade0969027648a3fa", "rule_source": "Sigma Integrated Rule Set (GitHub)", "rule_title": "Disable of ETW Trace", "rule_description": "Detects a command that clears or disables any ETW trace log which could indicate a logging evasion.", "rule_author": "@neu5ron, Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Jonhnathan Ribeiro, oscd.community", "match_context": [{"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe\" sl Security /e:false", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\wevtutil.exe", "EventID": "1"}}]}, {"rule_level": "medium", "rule_id": "d3e54936275abafa46d4b77891ec8f7fe6dd55d420fec613476144dd5d26f1a7", "rule_source": "Sigma Integrated Rule Set (GitHub)", "rule_title": "Deleted Data Overwritten Via Cipher.EXE", "rule_description": "Detects usage of the \"cipher\" built-in utility in order to overwrite deleted data from disk.\nAdversaries may destroy data and files on specific systems or in large numbers on a network to interrupt availability to systems, services, and network resources.\nData destruction is likely to render stored data irrecoverable by forensic techniques through overwriting files or data on local and remote drives\n", "rule_author": "frack113", "match_context": [{"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\cipher.exe\" /w:D:", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\cipher.exe", "EventID": "1"}}, {"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\cipher.exe\" /w:A:", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\cipher.exe", "EventID": "1"}}, {"values": {"CommandLine": "\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\cipher.exe\" /w:C:", "Image": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\cipher.exe", "EventID": "1"}}]}]}}}